        "timestamp": "2017-08-16 13:38:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJust because it's failing to build is no excuse for abandoning a change. It's always better to just work the issue until it passes than create new changes in Gerrit. Don't be ashamed of failures showing up, they happen!\n\nThe only time I personally believe a change should be abandoned is if it's truly a bad change that won't get merged or is in direct conflict with a better change / one that already fixes the issue that's trying to be addressed.",
